definition.value: A monoterpenoid that is the  acetate ester derivative of  geraniol.
A macromolecule derived from two or more species of monomer.

A copolymer macromolecule composed of homopolymeric blocks of 1->4-linked homopolymeric blocks of 1->4-linked sodium beta-D-mannuronate and sodium alpha-L-guluronate residues, covalently linked together in different sequences or blocks. The sodium salt of alginic acid.
A macromolecule composed of units connected by benzoxazole linkages.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 6-(1,3-benzoxazol-6-yl)-2-phenyl-1,3-benzoxazole units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating substituted or unsubstituted fluorene units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating trimethyl(6-{2-phenyl-9-[6-(trimethylazaniumyl)hexyl]-9H-fluoren-9-yl}hexyl)azanium dibromideyl}hexyl)azanium units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating fluorene-2,7-diyl units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating butyl propionate units.
A macromolecule containing exclusively alkenylene (alkene-alpha,omega-diyl) units. A polymer of the form [-CH=CH-(CH2)m-]n.
A macromolecule generated from the monomer 1,3-butadiene.
A macromolecule composed of repeating but-2-ene-1,4-diyl units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating butyl isobutyrate units.
A macromolecule composed of 2,2'-bithiophene units linked at the 5- and 5'-postions.
A macromolecule carrying multiple positive charges.
A (1->4)-beta-D-glucan compound composed of repeating beta-(1->4)-linked 6-azido-6-deoxyglucose units.
A (1->4)-beta-D-glucan compound formed by nitrating cellulose through exposure to nitric acid or another powerful nitrating agent.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3,4-dihydroxymandelic acid.
A heterocalix[4]aromatic compound composed of alternating 1,3-phenylene and 1,3,5-triazin-2,6-yl groups connected by ether linkages.
A heterocalix[4]aromatic compound composed of alternating 1,3-phenylene and 1,3,5-triazin-2,6-yl groups connected by amine linkages.
A heteroacene compound consisting of benzothiophene fused to anthracene in a rectilinear arrangement.

An organic heterotetracyclic compound consisting of a benzo[a]pyrimido[2,1,6-cd]pyrrolizine ring system having amino substituents at the 2- and 9-positions, trimethylsilyl substituents at the 5- and 7-positions and cyano substituents at the 3-, 4- and 8-postions.
A macromolecule prepared from substituted or unsubstituted acetylene (ethyne) units.
Macromolecule composed of repeating substituted or unsubstituted but-1-en-3-yne units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating methyl(3,3,3-trifluoropropyl)siloxane units.
A copolymer macromolecule composed of dimethylsiloxane and 3-(2-(2-hydroxyethoxy)ethoxy)propyl]methylsiloxane units.
The S enantiomer of 3-hydroxy-3-methyl-2-oxopentanoic acid.
A substance used to cause adherence of tissue to tissue or tissue to non-tissue surfaces, as for prostheses.
The conjugate base of 3-hydroxy-3-methyl-2-oxopentanoic acid.
Any fatty acid containing at least one C=C double bond.
A compound composed of linked vanadate units.
A polymer composed of repeating hydromethylsiloxane units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating N-methyl-N-propylpropan-1-aminium chloride units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 2-(diethylamino)ethyl isobutyrate units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 1,2-diiodobut-1-en-3-yne units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 2-(diisopropylamino)ethyl isobutyrate units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 2-(dimethylamino)ethyl isobutyrate units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 9,9'-dioctylfluorene-2,7-diyl units.
Any arenesulfonate oxoanion in which the arene moiety is benzene.
The organic sodium salt of 2,4-dinitrobenzenesulfonic acid.
A chromium chloride with the chromium cation in the +3 oxidation state.
Any of the chlorides of chromium.
A drug that binds to and activates gamma-hydroxybutyric acid receptors.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 2-hydroxyethoxyacetyl units, obtained via ring-opening polymerisation of p-dioxanone.
A macromolecule composed of repeating N,N-dimethyl-N-propylpropan-1-aminium chloride units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 2,5-bis(cholestanoxy)-1,4-phenylenevinylene units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 1-((2-ethylhexyl)oxy)-4-methoxy-2-vinylbenzene units.
A polymer composed of repeating butane-1,2-diyl units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating ethyl (2-hydroxyethyl) phosphonate units.
A poly(ethylene glycol) compound having a methacrylate group at the alpha-terminus and a methyl group at the omega-terminus.
